---
name: code-review
version: 1.0.0
description: Codex agent critical code review template. Read-only analysis — no code changes, no commits. Reports findings with BLOCKING/IMPORTANT/MINOR severity.
format: xml
required_variables:
  - task_id
  - review_id
  - assignee
  - description
  - scope
  - codebase_root
  - review_focus
  - references
---
<atm-code-review id="{{ task_id }}" review="{{ review_id }}" assignee="{{ assignee }}">
  <description>{{ description }}</description>

  <codebase-root>{{ codebase_root }}</codebase-root>
  <scope>{{ scope }}</scope>

  <review-focus>
{{ review_focus }}
  </review-focus>

  <references>
{{ references }}
  </references>

  <workflow>
    <step id="a">ACK this message immediately. This is a READ-ONLY review — do not commit, push, or modify any files.</step>
    <step id="b">Read the references listed above to understand the architecture, requirements, and design constraints before reviewing code.</step>
    <step id="c">Review the codebase at {{ codebase_root }} across the scope: {{ scope }}. Apply critical production-readiness judgment — flag issues that would prevent a 1.0 release.</step>
    <step id="d">
      Classify every finding:
      - BLOCKING: must be fixed before 1.0 release (correctness, safety, data integrity, API contract violations, missing error recovery)
      - IMPORTANT: should be fixed but does not block release (code quality, performance, maintainability)
      - MINOR: advisory, low-effort improvements
      For each finding include: severity, file:line, description, and recommended fix.
    </step>
    <step id="e">Send your complete findings report to team-lead. Format:
      VERDICT: PASS | FAIL (fail if any BLOCKING findings)
      BLOCKING findings (numbered list)
      IMPORTANT findings (numbered list)
      MINOR findings (numbered list)
      Overall production-readiness assessment for 1.0 release.
    </step>
  </workflow>
</atm-code-review>
